The paper proposes a novel neural network architecture for change detection in multispectral images, which involves learning joint spectral-spatial-temporal features. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves training a neural network to learn these features, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also involves analyzing temporal dependence in bitemporal images, which suggests that it may belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper involves remote sensing image analysis, which suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves adaptively learning temporal dependence between multitemporal images, which suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
